## Import Paths (CRITICAL)
- Always use `from app.X import Y` pattern for application code
- DO NOT use `from generated.project_name.app.X import Y` 
- DO NOT use absolute paths like `from /path/to/app.X import Y`
- Import from the module structure as if you're inside the project root

## Mocking and External Dependencies
- DO NOT mock or patch modules that don't exist in the codebase
- Only use `monkeypatch.setattr()` or `@patch()` on actual functions/modules that are imported in the code under test
- If you need to mock internal functionality, ensure the module path is correct and exists
- NEVER create placeholder modules like "some_module.some_function"

